caption: Table 1: Accuracy of models for average-case initial model parameters (θ0).
description: This table presents the accuracy achieved by models trained using DP-SGD with average-case initial model parameters.  The accuracy is shown for different values of epsilon (ε), representing the privacy level, for both the MNIST and CIFAR-10 datasets.  Higher accuracy values indicate better model performance, while higher epsilon values represent a weaker privacy guarantee. The data in this table is used for comparison with results obtained using worst-case initial parameters.

caption: Table 1: Accuracy of models for average-case initial model parameters (θ0).
description: This table shows the accuracy achieved by models using average-case initial model parameters (θ0) for different privacy levels (ε) on the MNIST and CIFAR-10 datasets.  The accuracy represents the percentage of correctly classified images in the test set.  The table highlights the trade-off between privacy and accuracy, showing that higher privacy levels (lower ε) generally lead to lower accuracy.
